.TH "snd_device_new" 9 "snd_device_new" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_device_new \- create an ALSA device component
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_device_new
.BI "(struct snd_card *card "  ","
.BI "enum snd_device_type type "  ","
.BI "void *device_data "  ","
.BI "const struct snd_device_ops *ops "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "card" 12
the card instance
.IP "type" 12
the device type, SNDRV_DEV_XXX
.IP "device_data" 12
the data pointer of this device
.IP "ops" 12
the operator table
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Creates a new device component for the given data pointer.
The device will be assigned to the card and managed together
by the card.

The data pointer plays a role as the identifier, too, so the
pointer address must be unique and unchanged.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero if successful, or a negative error code on failure.
